cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.PF, cs.SI, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a stochastic model to obtain the end-to-end delay law between two nodes of a Delay Tolerant Network (DTN) and focuses on the Binary Spray and Wait (BSW) routing protocol. This falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a model that can be applied to homogeneous or heterogeneous networks, which involves information theory concepts such as channel capacity and entropy. 
3. cs.PF (Physics and Society) - The paper proposes a stochastic model, which involves probability theory and statistical physics concepts. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with the delay distribution of a routing protocol in a network, which falls under the scope of social and information networks. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper deals with a routing protocol in a Delay Tolerant Network, which involves distributed computing concepts.
